docs.abstract: The chief executives for Johnson & Johnson and IBM said businesses had a responsibility to both employees and customers.
docs.snippet: The chief executives for Johnson & Johnson and IBM said businesses had a responsibility to both employees and customers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Communicating with employees is a bit like building a bank account, according to Alex Gorsky, the chief executive of Johnson & Johnson: making contributions over time, developing a reservoir of trust, because “someday you’re likely going to need to make a withdrawal.”
